[telegram] <Regnar> EVERYONE!! please be careful if you have input a seed phrase into Coinomi windows wallet (not sure of which other versions have this security flaw too) but apparently Coinomi seed input sends your seed phrase, in clear text(not encrypted), to Google's servers to spell check. I haven't verified the issue but a Komodo Dev, Luke Childs, has and shared on his Twitter so I'm passing it along here.
https://twitter.com/lukechilds/status/1100613365850767360?s=20
And here's the reported incident.
avoid-coinomi.com
"I would also strongly suggest anyone using Coinomi move your funds immediately to a different wallet. Your plain text seed phrase is quite likely sitting in a log file on Googles servers accessible to a large number of employees." - Luke Childs
